1
00:00:24,211 --> 00:00:28,591
Two households,
both alike in dignity,
"我们的故事发生在繁华的维洛纳城"

2
00:00:28,716 --> 00:00:35,099
in fair Verona
where we lay our scene,

3
00:00:31,156 --> 00:00:34,994
"那里有两大个家族，有相等的声望"

4
00:00:35,183 --> 00:00:40,105
from ancient grudge
break to new mutiny,
"从宿仇中又有新的嫌怨爆发"

5
00:00:40,189 --> 00:00:45,612
where civil blood
makes civil hands unclean.
"使得市民的血把清白的手弄脏"

6
00:00:45,696 --> 00:00:49,909
From forth the fatal loins
of these two foes...

7
00:00:48,007 --> 00:00:51,886
"命中注定，从这两家仇人的肚里"

8
00:00:51,704 --> 00:00:57,628
a pair of star-crossed lovers
take their life,

9
00:00:53,429 --> 00:00:57,975
"生出一对命运多桀情人"

10
00:00:57,712 --> 00:01:03,093
whose misadventured
piteous overthrows
"他们的不幸的悲惨的结局"

11
00:01:03,094 --> 00:01:09,101
do with their death...
bury their parents'strife.
"埋葬了两家父母的纠纷"

12
00:01:29,211 --> 00:01:32,131
But the quarrel is between
our masters and us their men.
这仇恨只是两家主人和男仆们之间的事

13
00:01:32,214 --> 00:01:34,425
Ah, 'tis all one.
都一样啦.

14
00:01:36,220 --> 00:01:39,432
Here come the house
of the Montagues.

15
00:01:38,142 --> 00:01:41,562
那边，蒙泰鸠家的人来了.

16
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:43,603
Ah, good morrow.

17
00:01:43,729 --> 00:01:45,522
Good morrow
to you, sir.
- 早安.
- 你早呀！先生.

18
00:01:45,523 --> 00:01:48,610
Quarrel,
I will back thee.

19
00:01:48,736 --> 00:01:50,112
Right.
找他们打架，我会在背后支持你.

20
00:01:50,237 --> 00:01:51,822
Fail me not.
不要怕我逃跑.

21
00:01:53,824 --> 00:01:55,910
来，上吧.

22
00:02:01,836 --> 00:02:05,131
Do you bite
your thumb at us, sir?
你是在对我们咬你的大拇指吗？
先生

23
00:02:05,132 --> 00:02:08,135
I do bite
my thumb, sir.

24
00:02:08,135 --> 00:02:13,141
Do you bite
your thumb at us, sir?
我是在咬我的大拇指，先生.

25
00:02:10,259 --> 00:02:13,220
你是冲着我们咬你的大拇指吗？
先…生

26
00:02:13,142 --> 00:02:15,645
No, sir.
不是的！先生, 我不是对你们咬我的大拇指
先生

27
00:02:15,645 --> 00:02:18,648
I do not bite my
thumb at you, sir,

28
00:02:18,649 --> 00:02:21,152
but I do bite
my thumb, sir.
但是我是在咬我的大拇指，先生.

29
00:02:21,152 --> 00:02:22,653
Do you quarrel, sir?
你想找打架吗，先生？

30
00:02:22,654 --> 00:02:28,119
Quarrel, sir?
No, no, no, sir.

31
00:02:26,441 --> 00:02:29,361
打架，先生！不，先生

32
00:02:28,245 --> 00:02:30,623
If you do, sir,
I am for you.
如果你想打架，先生
我可以奉陪

33
00:02:30,748 --> 00:02:32,625
I serve as good
a man as you.
- 我伺候的主人一点也不比你们的差
- 不见得更好一些吧

34
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:33,626
No better?

35
00:02:33,752 --> 00:02:35,921
Yes, better, sir.
是要更好一些

36
00:02:39,259 --> 00:02:42,137
You lie.
你说谎.

37
00:02:54,653 --> 00:02:56,154
Draw!

38
00:02:56,239 --> 00:02:57,824
Draw if you be men!
- 拔出剑来，如果你们是男子汉！!
- 别忘记使用你那一手绝招！

39
00:02:57,949 --> 00:02:59,742
Gregory, remember
thy swashing blow!

40
00:03:04,166 --> 00:03:06,126
Kill the Capulets!
杀了凯布雷！

41
00:03:21,646 --> 00:03:24,149
Part, fools!
Put up your swords!
蠢材！收起你们的剑！.
你们不知道你们干的是什么事！

42
00:03:24,150 --> 00:03:26,152
You know not what you do!

43
00:03:26,152 --> 00:03:28,154
The Prince hath
expressly forbid
公爵严禁在维洛纳的街上打斗

44
00:03:28,155 --> 00:03:30,241
this bandying
in Verona streets!

45
00:03:30,241 --> 00:03:32,160
Here come the Capulets!
凯布雷家的人来了！

46
00:03:34,246 --> 00:03:37,667
Tybalt, Capulet's kinsman!
提伯特，凯布雷的亲戚

47
00:03:44,759 --> 00:03:50,057
What, art thou drawn among
these heartless hinds?

48
00:03:46,607 --> 00:03:51,237
怎么？你也拔剑参加这群怯懦的奴才们的打斗吗？

49
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:55,648
Turn thee, Benvolio.
Look upon thy death.
- 转过身来，宾瓦利，准备受死吧
- 我只是在维持和平.

50
00:03:55,773 --> 00:03:57,149
I do but keep the peace.

51
00:03:57,275 --> 00:03:58,651
Put up thy sword
收起你的剑
再不就来帮我把他们分开

52
00:03:58,777 --> 00:04:01,071
or manage it
to part these men with me.

53
00:04:01,155 --> 00:04:03,866
What, drawn
and talk of peace?
什么！拔出了剑还要谈和平？

54
00:04:03,951 --> 00:04:05,369
I hate the word,

55
00:04:05,453 --> 00:04:09,875
as I hate hell,
all Montagues and thee.
我讨厌这个名词，就如同恨地狱
恨蒙泰鸠一家人，恨你，完全一样

56
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:11,459
Have at thee, cowards!
- 看剑，懦夫！
- 凯布雷！

57
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:13,253
Capulet!

58
00:04:13,379 --> 00:04:14,672
Montague!
蒙泰鸠！

59
00:04:17,051 --> 00:04:19,178
Capulet!

60
00:04:27,981 --> 00:04:29,858
Now hie thee home,
fragment.
- 现在，藏起你的头
- 恶棍！

61
00:04:29,984 --> 00:04:32,278
You villain!

62
00:04:36,075 --> 00:04:37,660
Capulet!

63
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:46,254
Give me my long sword! Ho!
把我的长剑给我，喂！
凯布雷！

64
00:04:46,380 --> 00:04:47,673
Capulet!
下去到市场广场！

65
00:04:47,757 --> 00:04:49,175
Down to the market square!

66
00:04:49,259 --> 00:04:51,178
Capulet!

67
00:04:51,261 --> 00:04:53,972
Follow me! Follow me!

68
00:04:53,973 --> 00:04:57,686
Kill that villain Montague!
杀了那些恶棍蒙泰鸠！

69
00:05:00,189 --> 00:05:03,067
My noble uncle!
My noble uncle!
伯父！…

70
00:05:03,193 --> 00:05:04,861
What?

71
00:05:04,987 --> 00:05:08,074
My sword! My sword!
什么？

72
00:05:06,607 --> 00:05:08,775
我的剑！…

73
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:12,079
Thou shalt not stir
a foot to seek a foe!

74
00:05:10,402 --> 00:05:13,030
不准你迈一步去寻仇！

75
00:05:12,163 --> 00:05:16,084
Hold me not!
Let me go!
别拉着我！让我去！

76
00:05:16,085 --> 00:05:18,087
Montague!

77
00:05:18,171 --> 00:05:19,672
Montague!
蒙泰鸠！

78
00:05:19,673 --> 00:05:21,174
Kill the villain!

79
00:05:45,998 --> 00:05:49,001
I'll strike thee, coward.
我要好好教训你，懦夫

80
00:06:04,188 --> 00:06:05,815
The Prince!

81
00:06:05,899 --> 00:06:08,110
The Prince is coming!
Put down your weapons!
- 公爵来了！
- 放下你们的武器！

82
00:06:08,193 --> 00:06:10,404
The Prince!

83
00:06:10,488 --> 00:06:12,615
The Prince!

84
00:06:15,119 --> 00:06:17,288
Here comes the Prince!
公爵来了！

85
00:06:17,288 --> 00:06:19,499
Put your weapons down!
The Prince!

86
00:06:26,717 --> 00:06:30,596
Rebellious subjects,
enemies to peace,
作乱的民众，治安的敌人

87
00:06:30,722 --> 00:06:33,225
throw your mistempered
weapons to the ground...
快将你们的血腥的手里的凶器…

88
00:06:33,225 --> 00:06:35,018
Down with your weapons.

89
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:40,526
And hear the sentence
of your moved Prince.
丢在地上

90
00:06:38,577 --> 00:06:42,205
听你们震怒的公爵的裁判

91
00:06:44,698 --> 00:06:49,203
Three civil brawls
bred of an airy word,
你们只是为了几句话
便发生三次斗殴

92
00:06:49,204 --> 00:06:50,705
by thee, old Capulet...

93
00:06:50,831 --> 00:06:52,416
No, no.
你老凯布雷…

94
00:06:56,005 --> 00:06:58,299
And Montague...
和老蒙泰鸠…

95
00:06:58,424 --> 00:07:01,594
Have thrice disturbed
the quiet of our streets.
三次扰乱街道上的和平

96
00:07:04,724 --> 00:07:08,103
If ever you disturb
our streets again,
如果你们再破坏街道上的安宁

97
00:07:08,229 --> 00:07:12,108
your lives shall pay
the forfeit of the peace.

98
00:07:10,026 --> 00:07:13,946
你们就要以生命来赎罪

99
00:07:12,234 --> 00:07:17,615
For this time
all the rest depart away!

100
00:07:14,488 --> 00:07:18,910
至于这一次，其余的人都走开

101
00:07:20,202 --> 00:07:23,706
You, Capulet,
shall go along with me.

102
00:07:21,704 --> 00:07:24,790
你，凯布雷，你跟我来

103
00:07:23,832 --> 00:07:26,210
And, Montague,
come you this afternoon.
而蒙泰鸠，你下午过来

104
00:07:29,214 --> 00:07:36,640
Once more, on pain of death,
all men depart.
再说一遍，一切人等全都走开

105
00:07:35,801 --> 00:07:38,346
否则处死

106
00:07:53,245 --> 00:07:56,248
Where is Romeo?
Saw you him today?

107
00:07:56,249 --> 00:07:59,711
Right glad I am
he was not at this fray.
罗蜜欧在哪里？
你今天看见他了吗？

108
00:07:58,075 --> 00:08:01,078
我很高兴他没有赶上这场打斗

109
00:07:59,836 --> 00:08:02,130
Madam, an hour before
the worshipped sun
夫人，在万人景仰的太阳
从东方金窗探头之前一小时

110
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:04,718
peered forth
the golden window of the east,

111
00:08:04,843 --> 00:08:08,138
a troubled mind drove me
to walk abroad:

112
00:08:08,222 --> 00:08:10,641
where, underneath
the grove of sycamore
我心里一阵烦躁
想起身出外散步

113
00:08:10,725 --> 00:08:12,852
so early walking
did I see your son.
在城西一带的枫树林的下面
我看到你儿子一早就在那里走动

114
00:08:12,937 --> 00:08:17,651
Towards him I made;
but he was ware of me,

115
00:08:15,259 --> 00:08:18,720
我向他走去，但他发觉我了

116
00:08:17,734 --> 00:08:19,653
and stole into
the cover of the wood.
就躲进林荫深处....

117
00:08:23,742 --> 00:08:27,621
Many a morning hath
he there been seen.
好几天一清早就有人在那里看见他

118
00:08:32,545 --> 00:08:34,631
See, where he comes.

119
00:08:34,237 --> 00:08:36,447
看，他来了

120
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:44,727
So please you, step aside.
请您暂且躲在旁处
我要问问他，看他究竟有些什么心事

121
00:08:44,727 --> 00:08:48,231
I'll know his grievance,
or be much denied.

122
00:08:48,232 --> 00:08:51,235
I would thou wert
so happy by thy stay,
愿你运气好，能听到他的真心话

123
00:08:51,236 --> 00:08:52,737
to hear true shrift.

124
00:08:52,738 --> 00:08:55,241
Come, madam. Let's away.

125
00:08:54,592 --> 00:08:56,886
来吧，夫人，我们走开吧！

126
00:09:26,865 --> 00:09:29,159
Good morrow, cousin.

127
00:09:29,586 --> 00:09:31,796
早安，表弟

128
00:09:34,249 --> 00:09:36,042
Is the day so young?

129
00:09:36,043 --> 00:09:37,878
But new struck nine.
- 现在还算早吗？
- 刚敲过九点

130
00:09:37,879 --> 00:09:39,172
Ay me!
唉呀！

131
00:09:41,258 --> 00:09:42,759
Sad hours seem long.
愁苦的时间似乎特别长

132
00:09:48,768 --> 00:09:51,271
Was that my father
that went hence so fast?
从这里急忙走开的可是我的父亲？

133
00:09:51,271 --> 00:09:52,772
Hmm?

134
00:09:52,773 --> 00:09:54,274
It was.
是的

135
00:10:01,659 --> 00:10:04,370
What sadness lengthens
Romeo's hours?

136
00:10:04,455 --> 00:10:11,380
Not having that, which having
makes them short.
有什么愁苦的事使得罗密欧的时间显得长？

137
00:10:06,749 --> 00:10:12,505
未能得到能使时间变短的东西

138
00:10:11,464 --> 00:10:14,551
Hmm. Hmm!

139
00:10:14,676 --> 00:10:16,261
But, Romeo...
- 但，罗蜜欧…
- 再见，表兄

140
00:10:16,387 --> 00:10:18,389
Farewell, Coz.

141
00:10:29,862 --> 00:10:31,781
God's me,
what fray was here?
唉啊，谁在这里打架了？
不用告诉我…

142
00:10:31,865 --> 00:10:33,283
Yet tell me not,

143
00:10:33,367 --> 00:10:36,287
for I have heard it all.
我已经全听说过了

144
00:10:37,872 --> 00:10:43,796
Here's much to do with hate,
but more with love.
这场冲突与仇恨有关

145
00:10:43,880 --> 00:10:47,593
Soft, I will go along.
但更大的冲突却是与爱情有关

146
00:10:46,290 --> 00:10:48,667
且慢，我要和你一同去

147
00:10:52,767 --> 00:10:56,271
But Montague is bound
as well as l,

148
00:10:54,798 --> 00:10:59,094
但是蒙泰鸠和我一样均已保证不再扰乱治安
违犯时受同样的惩罚

149
00:10:56,396 --> 00:10:59,274
in penalty alike,

150
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,277
and 'tis not hard, I think,

151
00:11:01,277 --> 00:11:04,781
for men as old as we
to keep the peace.
我想，像我们这样年老的人
和平相处并不困难

152
00:11:04,782 --> 00:11:05,783
Oh...

153
00:11:05,783 --> 00:11:08,286
Of honorable reckoning
are you both,
你们二位都是德高望重的

154
00:11:08,286 --> 00:11:11,790
and pity 'tis you
lived at odds so long:

155
00:11:09,981 --> 00:11:14,194
这样久彼此不睦，实在是一件憾事

156
00:11:11,791 --> 00:11:15,796
but, but now, my lord,

157
00:11:15,796 --> 00:11:17,798
what say you to my suit?
不过，老伯…
你对我的请求，意下如何呢？

158
00:11:17,882 --> 00:11:20,802
But saying o'er what
I have said before,
我还是重复我说过的那一句话

159
00:11:20,886 --> 00:11:24,974
my child is yet
a stranger in the world.

160
00:11:22,911 --> 00:11:26,039
小女尚不懂事

161
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:29,772
She hath not seen the change
of fourteen years.

162
00:11:27,874 --> 00:11:30,877
她还不满十四岁呢

163
00:11:34,195 --> 00:11:37,282
Let two more summers
wither in their pride,

164
00:11:37,407 --> 00:11:39,200
'ere we may think her
ripe to be a bride.
再等两个夏季的花草变得焦黄
她才算得成熟，才好做新娘

165
00:11:39,285 --> 00:11:41,996
Younger than she
are happy mothers made.
比她年轻的小姐们都已做了母亲

166
00:11:50,090 --> 00:11:53,803
And too soon marred
are those so early made.
这样早就结婚的人实在是太早就被毁掉了

167
00:11:53,887 --> 00:11:56,807
The earth hath swallowed
all my hopes but she,
我的儿女均已被黄土所埋葬

168
00:11:56,890 --> 00:11:59,810
she is the hopeful lady
of my earth.

169
00:11:59,894 --> 00:12:03,315
But woo her, gentle
Paris, get her heart,
只剩了她，是我唯一的指望

170
00:12:03,315 --> 00:12:06,819
my will to her consent
is but a part.
向她求婚吧，好巴利斯，赢取她的心.
我是否同意要看她自己肯不肯

171
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:09,323
Oh, Peter!

172
00:12:09,323 --> 00:12:12,785
This night I hold
an old accustomed feast
噢，彼得！

173
00:12:11,001 --> 00:12:14,004
今晚我照例设宴款待来宾

174
00:12:12,786 --> 00:12:15,289
whereto I have invited
many a guest.
邀请了许多我喜欢的客人
你，也是我的客人中的一个

175
00:12:15,289 --> 00:12:18,292
Such as I love,
you among the store,

176
00:12:18,293 --> 00:12:21,296
one more, most welcome,
makes my number more.
如蒙赏光，当令我的宴席生色

177
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:31,100
Nurse,
where's my daughter?

178
00:12:31,226 --> 00:12:33,312
Call her forth to me.
奶妈，我的女儿在哪里？
叫她来见我

179
00:12:33,396 --> 00:12:35,315
Now, by my maidenhead
at 12 years old,
我指着我12岁时的童贞来发誓
我已经叫过她了

180
00:12:35,398 --> 00:12:36,816
I bade her come.

181
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:40,321
Where is the girl?
Juliet! Juliet!
这孩子哪里去了？
茱丽叶！…

182
00:12:40,321 --> 00:12:44,534
Where is the girl?
Juliet!
这孩子哪里去了？茱丽叶！

183
00:12:44,618 --> 00:12:48,831
Where is the girl? Juliet!
茱丽叶！这个孩子哪里去了？

184
00:12:47,248 --> 00:12:49,333
茱丽叶！

185
00:12:48,916 --> 00:12:51,335
How now, who calls?

186
00:12:51,419 --> 00:12:53,421
Your mother!
Your lady mother!
- 什么事，谁在叫呢？
- 你的妈妈，你的亲娘！

187
00:13:05,312 --> 00:13:08,315
Juliet, it's your mother,
your lady mother.
你的妈妈，你的亲娘！

188
00:13:08,315 --> 00:13:10,317
Make haste, girl.
Make haste.
快点，孩子，快点…
你在哪？

189
00:13:10,318 --> 00:13:12,111
Where were you?

190
00:13:14,323 --> 00:13:18,328
Madam, I am here.
What is your will?
妈妈，我在这里
你找我？

191
00:13:18,328 --> 00:13:20,831
This is the matter.

192
00:13:20,574 --> 00:13:22,701
是一件大事

193
00:13:22,834 --> 00:13:25,337
Make haste, girls.
Come on, come on.
- 快点，女孩们，快点…
- 奶妈

194
00:13:25,337 --> 00:13:26,421
Nurse, um...

195
00:13:26,422 --> 00:13:29,217
give leave awhile,
we must talk in secret.
你暂且离开一下
我们要私下里谈一谈

196
00:13:36,935 --> 00:13:39,813
Nurse, come back again.
I have remembered me.
奶妈，你回来，我想起来了

197
00:13:39,939 --> 00:13:43,318
Thou's hear our counsel.

198
00:13:43,444 --> 00:13:45,321
Thou knowest my daughter's
of a pretty age.
你要听听我们的谈话.
你知道我的女儿年纪不算小了

199
00:13:45,446 --> 00:13:47,323
I can tell her age
unto an hour.
- 当然，讲到她的年纪，我可以按钟头计算出来
- 她未满十四岁

200
00:13:47,449 --> 00:13:48,742
She's not fourteen.

201
00:13:48,951 --> 00:13:50,744
I'll lay fourteen
of my teeth.
我用我的十四颗牙齿打赌

202
00:13:50,828 --> 00:13:52,747
And yet to
my teen be it spoke,
说来好惨我只剩四颗了，她未满十四岁
现在离收获节还有多久？

203
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:54,750
I have but four,
she's not fourteen.

204
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:56,418
How long is it
to Lammastide?

205
00:13:56,544 --> 00:13:58,254
A fortnight and odd days.
- 还有二个星期零几天
- 零一天也好零两天也好

206
00:13:58,338 --> 00:14:00,632
Even or odd, of all
the days of the year,

207
00:14:00,758 --> 00:14:02,635
come Lammas Eve at night
shall she be fourteen.
只要到了收获节的前夕，她就满了十四岁

208
00:14:02,718 --> 00:14:04,136
Susan and she--
苏珊和她....
"愿上帝安息一切信仰基督的灵魂"....是同龄

209
00:14:04,220 --> 00:14:06,639
God rest all Christian
souls were of an age.

210
00:14:06,724 --> 00:14:09,143
Well, Susan is with God.
She was too good for me.
唉，苏珊现在是和上帝在一起了
像她这样的好孩子我无福消受

211
00:14:09,227 --> 00:14:11,020
But, as I said,
on Lammas Eve

212
00:14:11,146 --> 00:14:13,232
at night
shall she be fourteen.
不过，我才说过，
到了收获节的前夕她就是十四岁了

213
00:14:13,232 --> 00:14:15,443
That shall she, marry!
I remember it well.
她满十四岁，真是的，我记得清清楚楚

214
00:14:15,527 --> 00:14:19,156
My lord and you
were then at Mantua!
当时老爷和您都在曼酋亚
哼，我的记性不坏

215
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:21,743
Nay, I do bear a brain.

216
00:14:21,743 --> 00:14:24,246
For then she could,
she could stand high lone.
那时候她已经能独自站起来

217
00:14:24,246 --> 00:14:27,249
Nay, by the road she could have
run and waddled all about,
岂止站起来，我敢发誓，她能到处跑了

218
00:14:27,250 --> 00:14:30,253
for even the day before
she broke her brow;
就在那前一天，她跌破了头皮

219
00:14:30,254 --> 00:14:34,133
and then my husband-- God rest his soul,
'a were a merry man--
随后我的丈夫...."愿上帝守护他的灵魂"
他是个老好人

220
00:14:34,259 --> 00:14:35,635
took up the child.
就把孩子抱起来了

221
00:14:35,761 --> 00:14:39,265
"Yea," quoth he,
"dost thou fall upon thy face?

222
00:14:37,611 --> 00:14:41,156
对了，他说"你向前扑倒了？"

223
00:14:39,265 --> 00:14:42,143
"Thou wilt fall backward
when thou hast more wit;

224
00:14:42,269 --> 00:14:43,228
wilt thou not, Jule?"
你将来更懂事一些的时候，
将会仰面向后倒哩，你会不会

225
00:14:43,229 --> 00:14:45,231
Nurse!

226
00:14:45,231 --> 00:14:46,732
And by my holiday,
哎啊我的圣母
这小东西停住了哭，说"我会"

227
00:14:46,733 --> 00:14:49,236
the pretty wretch left
crying and said, "Ay."

228
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:56,245
Enough of this,
I pray thee hold thy peace.
- 够了，请你别说了
- 是的，夫人

229
00:14:56,371 --> 00:14:58,874
Yes, madam.

230
00:14:58,957 --> 00:15:02,544
Now, Juliet.

231
00:15:01,845 --> 00:15:03,680
现在，茱丽叶

232
00:15:04,256 --> 00:15:06,675
God mark thee to His grace

233
00:15:06,759 --> 00:15:10,138
Thou was the prettiest babe
that 'er I nurs'd.
愿上帝特别祝福你

234
00:15:08,476 --> 00:15:12,272
你是我奶过的最漂亮的孩子

235
00:15:10,138 --> 00:15:12,140
And I might live to see
thee married once,

236
00:15:12,266 --> 00:15:14,143
I have my wish.
如果我能活到看着你结婚
我就心满意足了

237
00:15:14,143 --> 00:15:20,651
Marry, that "marry" is the very theme
I came to talk of.

238
00:15:15,817 --> 00:15:21,531
说的是啊，我来正是要谈这结婚的问题

239
00:15:20,777 --> 00:15:21,945
Tell me,
daughter Juliet,
告诉我，茱丽叶我的孩子
你对于婚事有什么意见？

240
00:15:22,070 --> 00:15:25,157
how stands your disposition
to be married?

241
00:15:32,751 --> 00:15:35,254
It is an honor
that I dream not of.
- 那是我作梦也没想到的光荣
- 光荣

242
00:15:35,254 --> 00:15:37,757
An honor, were I not
thy only nurse,

243
00:15:37,757 --> 00:15:40,677
I would say thou hadst sucked
wisdom from my teat.
如果我不是你唯一的奶妈
我要说，你的智慧是从奶头上得来的

244
00:15:40,761 --> 00:15:43,264
Well, think
of marriage now.
好了，现在想一想结婚的事
在这维洛纳，比你年轻....

245
00:15:43,264 --> 00:15:46,267
Younger than you, here in Verona,
ladies of esteem,

246
00:15:46,268 --> 00:15:47,769
are made
already mothers.
有名望的小姐们
都已经做了母亲

247
00:15:47,770 --> 00:15:50,273
By my count
I was your mother

248
00:15:50,273 --> 00:15:53,276
much upon these years
that you are now a maid.
我在你如今做小姐的年龄
已经做了你的母亲

249
00:15:53,277 --> 00:15:54,778
Oh, yes, I remember.
- 是了，我记得
- 那么简单说吧

250
00:15:54,779 --> 00:15:57,574
Thus then, in brief...

251
00:15:57,658 --> 00:16:00,578
the valiant Paris
seeks you for his love.

252
00:16:00,578 --> 00:16:05,667
A man, young lady!
Lady, such as all the world--
- 英勇的巴利斯要向你求爱
- 真是个好男人，小姐

253
00:16:05,793 --> 00:16:07,670
Why he's a man of wax.
小姐，这个人是世界少有…
噢，他是个完人

254
00:16:07,754 --> 00:16:09,673
Verona's summer hath
not such a flower.
- 维洛纳的夏天不曾有过这样的一朵花
- 唉，他是一朵花

255
00:16:09,756 --> 00:16:11,675
Nay, he's
a flower in faith.

256
00:16:11,759 --> 00:16:13,177
Shh.

257
00:16:13,261 --> 00:16:18,183
What say you?
Can you love the gentleman?

258
00:16:15,587 --> 00:16:19,258
你怎么说？
你能不能爱这个人？

259
00:16:19,769 --> 00:16:21,562
Madam! Madam!
夫人…

260
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:23,690
The guests have come,
supper serv'd up,
客人到齐了，晚餐也上好了
大家在请您，也问起小姐...

261
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:25,860
you call'd,
my young lady ask'd for!

262
00:16:25,986 --> 00:16:28,197
We follow.
我们就去

263
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:32,285
Speak briefly,
can you like of Paris' love?

264
00:16:29,977 --> 00:16:33,772
简单说
你是否接受巴利斯的爱情？

265
00:16:32,285 --> 00:16:37,792
I'll look to like,
if looking liking move.

266
00:16:35,232 --> 00:16:39,570
看看再说，也许他能把我感动

267
00:16:37,792 --> 00:16:41,296
But no more deep
will I endart mine eye,

268
00:16:39,695 --> 00:16:42,531
但是我的眼光也不会投射太深

269
00:16:41,297 --> 00:16:44,300
than your consent gives
strength to make it fly.
除非是先得到了你的允许

270
00:16:47,805 --> 00:16:50,767
Juliet, the county stays.
- 茱丽叶，伯爵在等候
- 妈妈，我来了

271
00:16:50,767 --> 00:16:52,268
Madam, I come.

272
00:16:53,771 --> 00:16:58,777
Go, girl, seek happy nights
for happy days.
去，孩子，白天享福，夜间也要享受

273
00:17:21,014 --> 00:17:24,476
Give me a case
to put my visage in;
给我一个面具罩上我的脸

274
00:17:24,477 --> 00:17:26,479
a visor for a visor.
丑脸人都要嫌弃的丑面具

275
00:17:26,605 --> 00:17:31,194
What care I what curious eye
doth quote deformities.

276
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:32,166
我何必介意
如果有人好奇的注意看我这一副丑态

277
00:17:31,319 --> 00:17:34,698
Here are the beetle-brows
shall blush for me.
也还有这个突出的鬼脸替我遮羞

278
00:17:34,782 --> 00:17:36,283
Ahh!

279
00:17:38,704 --> 00:17:40,706
What, shall this speech
be spoke for our excuse?
怎么样，我们就拿这一套话做为藉口
还是根本不带歉意昂然而入？

280
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:42,792
Or shall we on
without apology?

281
00:17:42,792 --> 00:17:44,585
The date is out
of such prolixity.
这种累赘的虚文已经过时了
随便他们把我们当做什么人

282
00:17:44,711 --> 00:17:46,504
Let them measure us
by what they will.

283
00:17:46,589 --> 00:17:48,800
We'll measure them
a measure and be gone.
别想太多，我们跳他们一场舞就走

284
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:51,803
Come, knock and enter,
and no sooner in,

285
00:17:51,804 --> 00:17:55,600
but every man
betake him to his legs.
来吧，敲门进去，一进去之后
每个人都立刻就跳

286
00:17:55,726 --> 00:17:58,312
And we mean well in
going to this masque,
我们到这舞会，用意当然很好

287
00:17:58,312 --> 00:17:59,688
but 'tis no wit to go.
- 但是最好不要去
- 为什么？我要讨教？

288
00:17:59,814 --> 00:18:01,524
Why, may one ask?

289
00:18:01,608 --> 00:18:05,696
I dreamt a dream tonight.

290
00:18:05,697 --> 00:18:07,490
Ho, and so did I.
- 昨晚我做了一个梦
- 噢，我也是

291
00:18:07,616 --> 00:18:11,120
Well, what was yours?

292
00:18:11,204 --> 00:18:14,499
That dreamers often lie.
啊，你梦见了什么？

293
00:18:12,290 --> 00:18:15,544
做梦的人常胡言乱语

294
00:18:14,625 --> 00:18:19,214
In bed asleep while they
do dream things true.
在睡觉时可以梦见真实的东西

295
00:18:19,214 --> 00:18:22,801
Oh, then I see Queen Mab
hath been with you.

296
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:24,511
噢…那么"仙姑"必曾和你在一起

297
00:18:22,927 --> 00:18:25,513
Queen Mab?

298
00:18:25,597 --> 00:18:31,104
She is...She is
the fairies' midwife.
仙姑！她是谁？

299
00:18:26,806 --> 00:18:28,808
她是…

300
00:18:29,892 --> 00:18:33,271
她是…一个小仙的接生婆

301
00:18:32,815 --> 00:18:34,233
And she comes in state
她的身体不比一位市议员…

302
00:18:34,233 --> 00:18:36,736
no bigger than
an agate stone

303
00:18:36,737 --> 00:18:38,697
on the forefinger
of an alderman,
食指上戴的一块玛瑙为大

304
00:18:38,823 --> 00:18:42,035
drawn with a team
of little atomies

305
00:18:42,118 --> 00:18:45,330
athwart men's noses
as they lie asleep.
乘人睡觉的时候
驾着微尘般的小马拖曳的车子越过人们的鼻梁

306
00:18:45,414 --> 00:18:50,336
Her wagon spokes are made
of long spinner's legs;

307
00:18:47,410 --> 00:18:51,706
她的车辐是长脚蜘蛛的腿做的

308
00:18:50,337 --> 00:18:53,841
and the cover,
of the wings of grasshoppers;
车篷是蚱蜢的翅膀做的

309
00:18:53,842 --> 00:18:58,306
the traces
of the smallest spider's web;

310
00:18:56,086 --> 00:19:00,007
挽索是小蜘蛛网丝做的

311
00:18:58,306 --> 00:19:04,230
and the collars, mmm,
of the moonshine's watery beams;

312
00:19:00,132 --> 00:19:05,971
轭圈是水一般的月光做的

313
00:19:04,314 --> 00:19:06,733
her whip, crack!

314
00:19:06,817 --> 00:19:10,822
Is a cricket's bone;
the lash of film;
她的鞭子是蟋蟀的骨头做的

315
00:19:08,849 --> 00:19:11,727
鞭绳是游丝做的

316
00:19:10,947 --> 00:19:13,241
and in this state
用这样的排场
她夜夜的在情人的脑子里奔驰

317
00:19:13,242 --> 00:19:15,912
she gallops night by night
through lovers' brains,

318
00:19:16,037 --> 00:19:19,416
and then they dream of love,

319
00:19:17,608 --> 00:19:20,360
于是他们便做起了爱情梦

320
00:19:19,541 --> 00:19:23,921
o'er ladies' lips,
who straight on kisses dream,
走过女人的嘴唇
她们便立刻梦到接吻

321
00:19:24,047 --> 00:19:29,428
which oft the angry Mab
with blisters plagues,

322
00:19:26,533 --> 00:19:30,454
可是发怒的仙姑
常使她们的嘴上生疮

323
00:19:29,513 --> 00:19:32,433
because their breaths
with, er,
因为他们的口里沾染了糖果的气息

324
00:19:32,516 --> 00:19:33,934
sweetmeats tainted are.

325
00:19:34,018 --> 00:19:37,439
Snd sometime comes she
with a tithe-pig's tail,
有时候她在牧师睡觉之际

326
00:19:37,523 --> 00:19:40,443
tickling the parson's nose
as he lies asleep,
用抵租税的猪尾巴来搔他的鼻孔

327
00:19:40,527 --> 00:19:45,658
and dreams he
of another benefice.
于是他梦到一个更肥的牧师职位

328
00:19:45,658 --> 00:19:49,454
Amen.

329
00:19:47,305 --> 00:19:51,142
阿....门

330
00:19:51,124 --> 00:19:53,835
Sometimes she driveth
o'er a soldier's neck,
有时候她经过一个士兵的脖子

331
00:19:53,961 --> 00:19:55,337
and then dreams he

332
00:19:55,421 --> 00:19:58,842
of cutting foreign throats,
of breaches,
于是他梦到砍外国人的头
梦到突破工事

333
00:19:58,842 --> 00:20:02,054
ambuscadoes, spanish blades,
drums in his ear,
埋伏，梦到西班牙制的利剑
然后忽然听见鼓声

334
00:20:02,054 --> 00:20:03,555
at which he starts and wakes;
从梦中惊醒，惊醒之后....

335
00:20:03,556 --> 00:20:07,060
and being thus frighted
tries a prayer or two...

336
00:20:06,909 --> 00:20:09,119
咒骂了两句

337
00:20:12,025 --> 00:20:14,528
and sleeps again.
然后又睡着了

338
00:20:14,529 --> 00:20:16,531
This is that very Mab

339
00:20:16,531 --> 00:20:19,534
that plaits the manes
of horses in the night,
就是这仙姑
在夜间把马鬃编成辫结

340
00:20:19,535 --> 00:20:23,540
and bakes the elf-locks
in foul sluttish hairs,

341
00:20:21,131 --> 00:20:24,426
使得肮脏的女人的头发结成乌糟的一团

342
00:20:23,540 --> 00:20:27,169
which once untangled
much misfortune bodes.
这缠结便将是不祥之兆

343
00:20:27,253 --> 00:20:31,550
This is the hag,
when maids lie on their backs,

344
00:20:28,973 --> 00:20:32,851
就是这妖婆，在少女仰着睡的时候

345
00:20:31,634 --> 00:20:35,055
that presses them
and learns them first to bear
压在她们身上，教她们如何受孕

346
00:20:35,138 --> 00:20:39,560
making them women
of good carriage.

347
00:20:36,815 --> 00:20:39,734
使她们成为善于生育的妇人

348
00:20:39,644 --> 00:20:41,354
This is she...

349
00:20:41,438 --> 00:20:44,567
This is she that...
就是她…就是她…

350
00:20:44,651 --> 00:20:48,364
This...is she.
就是…

351
00:20:55,665 --> 00:20:58,043
Peace, Mercutio, peace.
别说了，马丘修，别说了

352
00:20:58,168 --> 00:21:00,546
Thou talk'st of nothing.
你是在胡说

353
00:21:00,546 --> 00:21:05,051
Thou talk'st of nothing.

354
00:21:02,340 --> 00:21:05,802
你是在胡说

355
00:21:07,555 --> 00:21:09,265
True.

356
00:21:09,265 --> 00:21:13,562
True, I talk of dreams;
是啊！我是在说梦

357
00:21:13,563 --> 00:21:17,568
which are the children
of an idle brain...

358
00:21:15,730 --> 00:21:19,483
梦原是无聊的头脑之胡思乱想…

359
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:23,575
Begot of nothing
but vain fantasy;

360
00:21:20,610 --> 00:21:23,946
只是空虚的幻想的产物

361
00:21:23,576 --> 00:21:28,081
which is as thin
of substance as the air,
其本质如空气一般的稀薄

362
00:21:28,081 --> 00:21:31,084
and more inconstant
than the wind

363
00:21:29,619 --> 00:21:32,371
比风还不稳定

364
00:21:31,169 --> 00:21:34,590
who woos even now
the frozen bosom of the north,
刚刚投向北方的冰冻的胸怀

365
00:21:34,673 --> 00:21:38,552
and being angered
puffs away from thence,

366
00:21:36,334 --> 00:21:39,754
忽然不高兴了，气冲冲的走开了

367
00:21:38,678 --> 00:21:41,556
turning his side
to the dew-dropping south.
转脸走向雨露繁多的南方

368
00:21:45,979 --> 00:21:50,067
This wind you talk of
blows us from ourselves.
你所说的这风把我们吹得离题太远了

369
00:21:50,193 --> 00:21:54,072
Strike drum.
Come, lusty gentlemen.
打起鼓来

370
